<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258570>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. (A) Scomberomorus guttatus (Bloch & Schneider, 1801) infected by Lernaeenicus alatus Rangnekar, 1962; (B, C, D) enlarged view of infection sites on the body and caudal fin. Lernaeenicus alatus: (E) habitus, dorsal; (F) head, dorsal; (G) head, ventral; (H) trunk, hind end." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258570/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258571>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Lernaeenicus anchoviellae Sebastian & George, 1964: (A) head, lateral; (B) head, ventral; (C) trunk, hind end." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258571/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258572>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lernaeenicus hemirhamphi Kirtisinghe, 1932 infecting three different hosts: (A) Hemiramphus far (Forsskål, 1775); (B) H. lutkei Valenciennes in Cuvier & Valenciennes, 1847 a; (C) Euleptorhamphus viridis (van Hasselt, 1823 b). Lernaeenicus hemirhamphi: (D) head, dorsal; (E) head, ventral; (F) trunk, hind end." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258572/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258573>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Lernaeenicus polynemi Bassett-Smith, 1898: (A) habitus; (B) trunk; (C) head, dorsal view; (D) hind end with egg strings; (E) hind end." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258573/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258574>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. (A) Lernaeenicus seeri Kirtisinghe, 1934 infecting Acanthocybium solandri (Cuvier in Cuvier & Valenciennes, 1832). Lernaeenicus seeri: (B) enlarged view; (C) habitus; (D) head, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258574/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.258575>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. (A) Lernaeenicus stromatei Gnanamuthu, 1953 infecting cloaca of Parastromateus niger (Bloch, 1795). Lernaeenicus stromatei: (B) enlarged cloacal region; (C) head, dorsal view; (D) head, lateral view; (E) hind end of trunk." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/258575/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

